AIM:
To create a Birthday card using html and css.

ALGORITHM:
Step 1: First open the vs code or any code editor.
Step 2: Design your Birthdat card.
Step 3: Type your html code.
Step 4: Then type your css code according to your desire.
Step 5: Execute the file and get the desired output.

CODE:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
 <title>Birthday Card</title>
 <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com"
crossorigin>
<link
href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Euphoria+Script&
display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body style="height: 100vh; background-color: #FDF4F5; display: 
flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
 <div>
 <div style="border: #BA90C6 2px solid; height: 600px; 
width: 900px; position: absolute; transform: rotate(3deg); 
"></div>
 <div style="position: relative; height: 600px;width: 
900px; display: flex; justify-content: start; flex-direction: 
column; align-items: center; border: #a020c4 2px solid; 
background-color: #FDF4F5;">
 <img src="https://www.pngkit.com/png/full/4-
45756_birthday-png.png" alt="" style="height: 300px; width: 
900px; object-fit: cover;">
 <h1 style="color: #BA90C6; font-family:monospace; 
font-size: 40px; margin: 0; line-height: 0px;">Happy</h1>
 <h1 style=" font-family: 'Euphoria Script', 
cursive; font-size: 124px; font-weight: 100; line-height: 
100px; margin: 20px; ">Birthday</h1>
 <i><p style="font-family: cursive; font-size: 20px; 
max-width: 800px; text-align: center;">I wish nothing but 
wonderful things on your special day. May the year shines 
bright for you. Wishing your days are bessed throughout the 
year.</p></i>
 </div>
 </div>
</body>
</html>

